								<p>‚ÄúThey have no idea how to work with a real design team.‚Äù We‚Äôve all heard or said something like that about people on our product teams, especially developers. While that‚Äôs a natural response to a breakdown in communication or a road bump during implementation, over time it can create an ‚ÄúUs vs. Them‚Äù mentality that does more harm than good. So how do we avoid scratching the itch. How do we keep avoiding giving in to the cynicism? As a design leader, how do you balance your team‚Äôs frustrations and continue to motivate them to deliver quality user experiences?</p>
